<taxonomicName authority="Richters 1904" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1904" box="[151,606,151,177]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="merokensis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,606,151,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,428,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Echiniscus merokensis</emphasis>
Richters 
<number box="[548,606,151,177]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,618]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
A total of 
<specimenCount box="[317,490,192,218]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="generic">
<number box="[317,361,192,218]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="679.0">679</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
were recorded from LF, MR, LR, MT and LT samples. I identified both 
<taxonomicName authority="Richters 1904" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1904" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="subSpecies" species="merokensis" subSpecies="merokensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Echiniscus merokensis merokensis</emphasis>
Richters 
<number box="[576,635,232,258]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</taxonomicName>
(with the typical morphotype: lateral filaments at positions C, D and E and dorsal spines at C and D; 
<figureCitation box="[546,639,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURE 5 A" captionStartId="13.[151,255,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,378,1962]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[164,1429,378,1962]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 5 A. Morphological variability found in Echiniscus merokensis. Percentages are provided for each morphotype. Arrows indicate missing appendages. (A) Echiniscus merokensis merokensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181850/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[602,616,272,298]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0">5</number>
A
</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Thulin 1911" authorityName="Thulin" authorityYear="1911" box="[709,1230,272,298]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="subSpecies" species="merokensis" subSpecies="suecica">
<emphasis box="[709,1074,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Echiniscus merokensis suecica</emphasis>
Thulin 
<number box="[1172,1230,272,298]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1911.0">1911</number>
</taxonomicName>
(with the typical morphotype: lateral filaments at positions B, C, D and E and dorsal spines at C and D; 
<figureCitation box="[1198,1291,312,338]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 5 A" captionStart-1="FIGURE 5 B" captionStartId-0="13.[151,255,1979,2003]" captionStartId-1="14.[151,255,683,707]" captionTargetBox-0="[164,1428,378,1962]" captionTargetBox-1="[188,1398,194,658]" captionTargetId-0="figure@13.[164,1429,378,1962]" captionTargetId-1="figure@14.[188,1398,194,659]" captionTargetPageId-0="13" captionTargetPageId-1="14" captionText-0="FIGURE 5 A. Morphological variability found in Echiniscus merokensis. Percentages are provided for each morphotype. Arrows indicate missing appendages. (A) Echiniscus merokensis merokensis." captionText-1="FIGURE 5 B. Morphological variability found in Echiniscus merokensis. Percentages are provided for each morphotype. Arrows indicate missing appendages. (B) Echiniscus merokensis suecica." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/181850/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/181851/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[1253,1268,312,338]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0">5</number>
B
</figureCitation>
). These two morphotypes appeared mixed in the same samples, but alone too. Additionally, I found a great variety within each morphotype of 
<taxonomicName box="[400,667,392,417]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="merokensis">
<emphasis box="[400,667,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Echiniscus merokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[685,888,392,418]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 5 A" captionStart-1="FIGURE 5 B" captionStartId-0="13.[151,255,1979,2003]" captionStartId-1="14.[151,255,683,707]" captionTargetBox-0="[164,1428,378,1962]" captionTargetBox-1="[188,1398,194,658]" captionTargetId-0="figure@13.[164,1429,378,1962]" captionTargetId-1="figure@14.[188,1398,194,659]" captionTargetPageId-0="13" captionTargetPageId-1="14" captionText-0="FIGURE 5 A. Morphological variability found in Echiniscus merokensis. Percentages are provided for each morphotype. Arrows indicate missing appendages. (A) Echiniscus merokensis merokensis." captionText-1="FIGURE 5 B. Morphological variability found in Echiniscus merokensis. Percentages are provided for each morphotype. Arrows indicate missing appendages. (B) Echiniscus merokensis suecica." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/181850/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/181851/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figs. 
<number box="[754,767,392,418]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0">5</number>
A and 
<number box="[852,867,392,418]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="5.0">5</number>
B
</figureCitation>
, respectively). Body size range of 
<taxonomicName class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="subSpecies" species="merokensis" subSpecies="merokensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Echiniscus merokensis merokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<number box="[484,611,432,458]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="418.0" valueMax="638.0" valueMin="198.0">198 to 638</number>
μm, mean 
<number box="[747,791,432,458]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="361.0">361</number>
μm (SD 
<number box="[902,934,432,458]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="63.0">63</number>
), while for 
<taxonomicName box="[1073,1436,432,457]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="subSpecies" species="merokensis" subSpecies="suecica">
<emphasis box="[1073,1436,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Echiniscus merokensis suecica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
body size ranged from 
<number box="[437,571,472,498]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="445.5" valueMax="693.0" valueMin="198.0">198 to 693</number>
μm, mean 
<number box="[714,758,472,498]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="356.0">356</number>
μm (SD 
<number box="[878,911,472,498]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="91.0">91</number>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[936,1205,472,497]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="merokensis">
<emphasis box="[936,1205,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Echiniscus merokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been cited for Europe, Asia, Africa and 
<collectingCountry box="[470,575,512,538]" name="United States of America" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">America</collectingCountry>
. In the Iberian Peninsula, 
<taxonomicName box="[904,1317,512,537]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="subSpecies" species="merokensis" subSpecies="merokensis">
<emphasis box="[904,1317,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Echiniscus merokensis merokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[301,400,552,578]" name="Portugal" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Da" box="[415,616,552,578]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" refString="Da Cunha, A. X. (1944 a) Tardigrados do Fauna Portuguesa II. Memorias e Estudos do Museu Zoologico da Universidade da Coimbra, 15, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1944" yearSuffix="a">
Da 
<collectingCountry box="[458,535,552,578]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cunha</collectingCountry>
<number box="[541,603,552,578]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1944.0">1944</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fontoura" box="[627,801,552,578]" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" refString="Fontoura, A. P. (1981) Contribution pour l'etudedes tardigrades terrestres du Portugal avec la description d'une nouvelle especie du genre Macrobiotus. Publicacoes do Instituto de Zoologia ' Dr. Augusto Nobre'. Facultad de Ciencias do Porto, 160,1 - 24." type="book" year="1981">
Fontoura 
<number box="[740,801,552,578]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1981.1982">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Fontoura" box="[813,875,552,578]" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" refString="Fontoura, A. P. (1982) Deux novelles especies de Tardigrades muscicoles du Portugal. Publicacoes do Instituto de Zoologia ' Dr. Augusto Nobre'. Facultad de Ciencias do Porto, 165, 5 - 19." type="journal article" year="1982">1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maucci" box="[886,1233,552,578]" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" refString="Maucci, W. &amp; Durante Pasa, V. (1984) Macrobiotus lusitanicus sp. nov. nuova specie di eutardigrado del portogallo nord - occidentale. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 11, 319 - 326." type="journal article" year="1984">
Maucci &amp; Durante Pasa 
<number box="[1172,1233,552,578]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1984.1985">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pasa" box="[1245,1305,552,578]" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" refString="Maucci, W. &amp; Durante Pasa, V. (1985) I Tardigradi della fauna Portoghese. Anais da Facultade de Ciencias, Universidade do Porto, 65 (1 / 4), 127 - 174." type="journal article" year="1985">1985</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1369,1436,552,578]" name="Spain" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Maucci" box="[159,512,592,618]" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" refString="Maucci, W. &amp; Durante Pasa, V. (1984) Macrobiotus lusitanicus sp. nov. nuova specie di eutardigrado del portogallo nord - occidentale. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 11, 319 - 326." type="journal article" year="1984">
Maucci &amp; Durante Pasa 
<number box="[449,512,592,618]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[532,797,592,617]" class="Heterotardigrada" family="Echiniscidae" genus="Echiniscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Echiniscoidea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="merokensis">
<emphasis box="[532,797,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Echiniscus merokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appeared at 
<number box="[945,974,592,618]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="20.0">20</number>
sampling points (Table 
<number box="[1257,1273,592,618]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0">3</number>
).
</paragraph>
